President Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. Amy L. Solomon is nominated for Assistant Attorney General of the Office of Justice Programs at the Department of Justice. Solomon has extensive experience in government, think tanks, and philanthropy, with a focus on social justice and improving the criminal justice system.

Milancy Harris is nominated for Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Security & Intelligence at the Department of Defense. She currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Irregular Warfare and Counterterrorism. Harris has worked in the intelligence community and has expertise in technology governance and content moderation.

Joey R. Hood is nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Tunisia. Hood is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has served in various leadership positions overseas, including in Iraq, Kuwait, and Saudi Arabia. He has experience in Iranian affairs, public affairs, and political-economic sections.

Jonathan Henick is nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Uzbekistan. He currently serves as the U.S. Department of State Chair at the College of Information and Cyberspace at the National Defense University. Henick has held positions in South and Central Asian affairs, global engagement, and international information programs.

Richard Glick is nominated for Member and Chair of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. He has been serving as Chairman since January 2021 and was previously nominated by President Trump in 2017. Glick has a background in energy policy and has worked in government affairs for renewable energy and utility companies.

These nominations reflect President Biden's commitment to selecting experienced individuals for key leadership roles in his administration.